1. Overview
This document summarizes the development and evaluation of multiple AI agents built using the Foundry SDK. It highlights the functionality of each agent, key challenges faced, and insights from evaluation including guardrails and Bing integration.
2. Agents Developed Using Foundry SDK
• Core Prompt Agent: Handles general user queries and generates contextual responses using LLM capabilities.

• Code Interpreter Tool Agent: सक्षम in executing code snippets, performing calculations, and handling file-based operations. This agent was used for data processing and analytical tasks.

• TMDB API Agent: Integrated with The Movie Database (TMDB) API to fetch movie-related information such as ratings, summaries, and recommendations. This agent enhances responses with structured external data.

• Weather Report Agent: Provides real-time weather information based on user queries by integrating with weather data sources.

• Bing-Integrated Agent: Uses web search capabilities to fetch up-to-date and relevant information, improving response accuracy for dynamic queries.

• Evaluation & Guardrails Agent: Ensures output quality, applies safety constraints, and validates responses against defined policies.
3. Key Challenges and Resolutions
• SDK API Changes: Encountered issues such as missing methods (e.g., thread creation). Resolved by adopting the updated Foundry SDK flow and correct API usage.

• Response Handling Issue: Outputs were not being displayed initially. Resolved by correctly parsing and printing the response object from the agent execution.
4. Bing Agent Analysis
The Bing-integrated agent significantly improved the system's ability to handle real-time queries. It provided accurate and enriched responses by leveraging external search data. However, it introduced slight latency due to API calls and required proper filtering of search results.
5. Guardrails Testing and Evaluation
Guardrails were tested to ensure safe and compliant outputs. They helped in restricting harmful content, maintaining response quality, and enforcing consistent behavior across agents. Evaluation confirmed improved reliability and trustworthiness.
6. Conclusion
The Foundry SDK enabled the development of multiple specialized agents, each serving a distinct purpose. The integration of APIs, tools, and guardrails resulted in a robust and scalable AI solution.
